@startuml
title Publish Court List v2.1 (multiple court sites per XML file)

' Change Log

' v2
' * Publishing Court Lists now saves the list to the 'published_court_list' table
' * XML files contain Court Lists for all Court Sites for the Parent Court
' * XML files are generated from Published Court Lists
' * The COURT_LIST_PRODUCED state is removed
' * The fileservice is removed

' Diagram changes
' * Status updates have been removed for clarity

' v2.1
' * Export is triggered by a scheduler to remove the race condition

ui.listing -> ListingCommandApi: listing.command.publish-court-list
ListingCommandApi -> ListingCommandHandler: listing.command.publish-court-list


ListingCommandHandler -> CourtListEventProcessor: listing.event.publish-court-list-requested (courtSite)
CourtListEventProcessor -> ListingQueryView: listing.query.unpublished-courtlist (courtSite)

note left
Query provided by SCSL-206
end note

' Store published court list
CourtListEventProcessor -> ListingCommandHandler: listing.command.store-published-court-list
ListingCommandHandler -> CourtListEventListener: listing.command.published-court-list-stored
participant "published_court_list" as published_court_list <<table>>
CourtListEventListener -> published_court_list: savePublishedCourtList

@enduml
